'.\" -*- nroff -*-
.TH KAFS-V6 8 "2026-07-02" "kafs 0.4.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
kafs-v6 \- dedicated format v6 runtime entrypoint
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kafs-v6
.RB --image
.I image
.B --inspection-mount
.I mountpoint
.BR -o " " ro
.RI [ FUSE\ options ]
.PP
.B kafs-v6
.RB --image
.I image
.B --controlled-write-mount
.I mountpoint
.BR -o " " rw,no_writeback_cache,no_trim_on_free,bg_dedup_scan=off,fsync_policy=full
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B kafs-v6
is the dedicated format v6 runtime entrypoint.
It validates the format v6 CLI boundary, rejects legacy
.B v6_*
mount-option mode tokens, runs descriptor preflight, and then admits the
selected v6 runtime contract.
.PP
Future format v6 runtime admission and write-surface work should move behind
this binary instead of broadening the production
.BR kafs (1)
binary.  The existing
.B kafs
binary remains the v4/v5 production runtime entrypoint.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Show help and exit.
.TP
.BR --image " " <image>
Specify the format v6 image path.
.TP
.BR --image= "<image>"
Specify the format v6 image path using the inline form.
.TP
.B --inspection-mount
Select the read-only v6 inspection contract.
The request must include
.BR -o " " ro .
.TP
.B --controlled-write-mount
Select the experimental v6 controlled write contract.
The request must include
.BR -o " " rw,no_writeback_cache,no_trim_on_free,bg_dedup_scan=off,fsync_policy=full .
.TP
.BR --option " " <opt[,opt...]>
Alias for FUSE
.BR -o .
.TP
.BR --option= "<opt[,opt...]>"
Inline form of
.BR --option .
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Help was printed.
.TP
.B 2
The request was invalid, the image was not format v6, descriptor preflight
failed, or runtime admission failed.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR kafs (1),
.BR mkfs.kafs (8),
.BR fsck.kafs (8),
.BR kafsdump (8)
.SH AUTHOR
kafs project.
